[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 18 points, a balanced hand, and a good stopper in their suit. He should overcall 1NT. 
For 1NT overcalls, the range is increased to 15-18 points.

SOUTH bids 2\C (Stayman), just as she would with a 1NT opening. When NORTH denies holding 
a 4-card Major SOUTH has enough points to bid 3NT. She doesn't worry about a \S stopper 
since NORTH promised he had the suit controlled.}

